32:29.822 --> 32:32.200
Is that the trace
of an East End accent I detect?

32:32.283 --> 32:33.117
Good ear.

32:33.201 --> 32:35.828
Mine was stamped out
in favor of the Queen's.

32:35.912 --> 32:37.664
Let me guess. Spitalfields?

32:37.747 --> 32:40.041
-Close. Whitechapel.
-You must know the Cat and Custard.

32:40.124 --> 32:42.251
-Next to the Fox and Hound.
-Best chippy in East London.

32:42.335 --> 32:45.004
I would murder for a spot of mushy peas
right about now.

32:45.088 --> 32:45.922
[both chuckle]

32:46.005 --> 32:48.299
So, how did you end up with this one?

32:48.383 --> 32:50.134
Well, we met in a mental hospital.

32:50.218 --> 32:51.260
I have no doubt.

32:51.344 --> 32:55.264
Well, he might be a few sandwiches short
of a picnic, but he'll do.

32:56.557 --> 32:57.558
Indeed.

33:04.107 --> 33:06.025
[Reginald] She's quite the specimen.

33:06.567 --> 33:07.819
Well done, my boy.

33:10.029 --> 33:11.239
Thanks, Dad.

33:11.322 --> 33:13.282
It is unfortunate timing.

33:14.575 --> 33:15.618
Why?

33:15.702 --> 33:17.745
You'd have made a superb father.

33:17.829 --> 33:19.831
[emotional instrumental music playing]

33:23.251 --> 33:25.878
Hey, Ben-ihana. Don't hit me! [chuckles]

33:25.962 --> 33:26.963
Hey, listen.

33:28.172 --> 33:32.010
I know we ain't exactly been best buds
in this timeline or whatever,

33:32.093 --> 33:34.303
but, man, do I have a mission for you--

33:34.387 --> 33:35.304
[belches]

33:35.888 --> 33:36.889
Ugh.

33:37.432 --> 33:38.516
Charming.

33:39.308 --> 33:40.935
-Ten people.
-Huh?

33:42.020 --> 33:44.272
-There are only ten people left.
-Okay.

33:44.355 --> 33:48.151
Drunk Ben clearly likes
numbers and… shrimp.

33:48.234 --> 33:52.071
And you couldn't even invite me
to your stupid bachelor party.

33:52.155 --> 33:52.989
Oh.

33:53.072 --> 33:57.410
Have we finally flicked off
bad Benny's hard candy shell?

33:57.493 --> 34:00.913
-Why don't you like me?
-Because you're a huge puckering asshole.

34:00.997 --> 34:03.458
-Okay, but you like the other Ben.
-Yeah, we love the other Ben.

34:03.541 --> 34:05.418
Why? What was so special about him?

34:05.501 --> 34:07.253
Because he was a know-it-all.

34:07.336 --> 34:08.921
He was a scold.

34:09.964 --> 34:14.802
He was a tiny dark cloud
on a perfect sunny day.

34:14.886 --> 34:16.137
[laughs]

34:18.222 --> 34:20.016
Those… Those are all bad things.

34:20.099 --> 34:21.768
Yeah, but they looked great on him.

34:21.851 --> 34:25.480
Okay, you know what?
I am so much better than that other Ben.

34:25.563 --> 34:27.648
-Mm-hmm?
-I was Number One.

34:28.441 --> 34:29.817
Twice.

34:29.901 --> 34:31.652
Does Dad give a shit?

34:32.236 --> 34:35.573
No. He was busy hanging out with you.

34:35.656 --> 34:39.952
Oh, man, methinks you might be
trying a little too hard.

34:40.036 --> 34:41.037
Look around.

34:41.120 --> 34:44.999
Nobody's polishing their boots
or pressing their tights.

34:45.083 --> 34:48.419
We're a complete and total shit show.
Ya get it?

34:48.503 --> 34:50.713
And our Ben, my Ben,

34:50.797 --> 34:52.757
was just that kinda disaster,

34:52.840 --> 34:55.885
and it made him ridiculously easy to love.

34:58.387 --> 34:59.722
[sighs]

35:04.143 --> 35:07.105
[departing footsteps]

35:11.526 --> 35:14.904
[clinking]

35:18.199 --> 35:19.534
-[taps on mic]
-[feedback whines]

35:21.702 --> 35:23.913
-[Reginald] I know it is customary…
-[Viktor] Hey.

35:23.996 --> 35:25.331
…for the father of the bride…

35:25.414 --> 35:27.125
-I'm not in the mood.
-Allison--

35:27.208 --> 35:29.377
No, I get it. It's a wedding.

35:29.460 --> 35:31.546
Everybody's drunk,
and we're all supposed to be chummy.

35:31.629 --> 35:33.714
-[Reginald's speech continues]
-But I'm not feeling it.

35:33.798 --> 35:37.135
That's fine.
You don't have to be in a festive mood.

35:38.386 --> 35:40.847
But will you please just hear me out?

35:42.390 --> 35:44.016
-[feedback whines]
-[clears throat]

35:44.892 --> 35:47.645
Sloane, ever since you were a little girl,

35:48.437 --> 35:51.315
I've always known
you were exceptionally bright.

35:51.399 --> 35:54.152
And though I can't say
I know Luther all that well,

35:54.235 --> 35:56.028
from the few moments we have shared,

35:56.112 --> 35:59.490
it seems you found yourself
an adequate partner.

36:00.074 --> 36:02.285
He just called Luther adequate. [snickers]

36:02.368 --> 36:03.870
Nicest thing he's ever said to him.

36:03.953 --> 36:06.706
-The kerchief really softens him though.
-Shh!

36:06.789 --> 36:11.669
I acknowledge that, as a father,
I was not without my faults.

36:12.503 --> 36:15.006
I hope these shortcomings

36:15.089 --> 36:20.052
will be seen as only a rough patch
on an otherwise verdant lawn.

36:21.053 --> 36:22.471
[Viktor] Look, I'm sorry.

36:22.555 --> 36:24.307
I was wrong.

36:24.390 --> 36:25.975
I lied, and…

36:27.727 --> 36:29.270
I betrayed your trust.

36:29.353 --> 36:31.731
[Reginald's speech continues faintly]

36:31.814 --> 36:33.065
But you're

36:33.941 --> 36:37.904
more important to me
than anything in this entire world.

36:40.323 --> 36:41.616
Will you forgive me?

36:44.452 --> 36:45.411
No.

36:47.413 --> 36:49.040
I don't think I will.

36:49.123 --> 36:51.542
I'm proud to call you my children.

36:52.668 --> 36:57.632
Even those whom I raised
in a revenant version of myself.

36:59.467 --> 37:04.931
I hope that tonight
we can create a few special memories

37:06.390 --> 37:09.352
in whatever precious little time
we have left.

37:09.435 --> 37:12.146
If you won't forgive me,
just know I forgive you.

37:12.230 --> 37:13.231
For what?

37:13.314 --> 37:14.607
[Reginald] And now, in closing…

37:14.690 --> 37:16.525
I didn't do anything wrong.

37:16.609 --> 37:17.902
You know, I'm

37:18.903 --> 37:22.114
really tired of being the asshole
that has to meet you halfway.

37:23.574 --> 37:27.036
-I am tired of being a sucker.
-You're the sucker?

37:27.119 --> 37:30.331
Our whole lives, all you said
you ever wanted was for us to be close,

37:30.414 --> 37:31.958
and we finally got there,

37:32.041 --> 37:34.418
and you fucked it up.

37:35.378 --> 37:36.587
Not me.

37:37.171 --> 37:39.048
Is this really how you wanna end things?

37:39.131 --> 37:41.467
Don't worry. I'll sleep fine tonight.

37:42.176 --> 37:45.513
[Reginald] The sun rises
over a lily's field.

37:46.472 --> 37:50.184
A mother veiled, her lips concealed.

37:51.769 --> 37:54.772
The mourners come in droves of black

37:55.690 --> 37:58.776
to bury what their hearts unpack.

37:58.859 --> 37:59.860
[bell dings]

38:00.403 --> 38:04.240
[Reginald] With shallow breath
and time eclipsed,

38:05.157 --> 38:09.787
I pray you miss death's gentle kiss.

38:10.538 --> 38:14.333
[emotional music swells]

38:17.628 --> 38:19.088
[Ben] That makes no sense.

38:19.171 --> 38:22.383
Beautiful! Bravo, Dad! Bravo!

38:22.466 --> 38:23.634
[applause continues]

38:23.718 --> 38:25.636
I didn't think the old man had it in him.

38:25.720 --> 38:26.804
[Chet] All right, all right.

38:26.887 --> 38:30.182
Time to turn those frowns upside down!

38:30.683 --> 38:34.437
This one is for all the party people
in the place.

38:35.771 --> 38:39.317
[emotional music continues playing]

39:44.131 --> 39:47.093
["Come In Mr. Lonely"
by Jerry Dyke playing]

39:47.176 --> 39:48.636
[feedback whines]

39:48.719 --> 39:50.221
[singing along] ♪ Come on in ♪

39:50.888 --> 39:53.224
♪ Sit right down ♪

39:53.766 --> 39:55.643
♪ Mr. Lonely ♪

39:56.227 --> 39:57.353
[Sloane moans softly]

39:58.687 --> 39:59.855
♪ You're too late… ♪

39:59.939 --> 40:02.817
-So, just to recap this night.
-Mm-hmm?

40:02.900 --> 40:05.069
Ben and Five are blotto drunk.

40:05.152 --> 40:07.363
[Luther chuckles heartily]

40:07.988 --> 40:09.532
[Five] ♪ Mr. Sadness… ♪

40:09.615 --> 40:14.203
And Viktor and Allison
almost punched each other out.

40:14.286 --> 40:15.996
-Oh. Yeah.
-Yeah.

40:16.580 --> 40:20.835
And Dad recited
a weirdly moving death poem.

40:21.752 --> 40:22.753
Hm.

40:24.964 --> 40:25.923
You know, that's not bad

40:26.006 --> 40:28.676
for a Hargreeves family wedding
at the end of the world.

40:30.886 --> 40:33.055
You know, I didn't need a big to-do.

40:35.683 --> 40:37.101
This is all I needed.

40:37.977 --> 40:43.941
[Five] ♪ I can't even offer you a smile… ♪

40:47.486 --> 40:48.904
That used to be us.

40:50.990 --> 40:52.408
We were never like that.

40:53.742 --> 40:54.577
Gross.

40:57.663 --> 40:59.039
That's more like it.

40:59.123 --> 41:03.961
♪ Who planned things this way? ♪

41:06.380 --> 41:07.631
♪ No offense ♪

41:08.507 --> 41:10.426
♪ But you know ♪

41:10.509 --> 41:12.845
♪ I'm still looking ♪

41:16.432 --> 41:18.684
[wind whistling]

41:21.562 --> 41:23.522
[Lila] It's probably a good thing.

41:24.690 --> 41:26.317
I would've been a shit mum.

41:30.946 --> 41:32.114
I doubt that.

41:32.198 --> 41:33.199
Hey, guys.

41:40.080 --> 41:41.081
Hey, uh…

41:42.082 --> 41:43.209
I saw.

41:43.709 --> 41:45.794
And I… I appreciate you trying.

41:47.213 --> 41:48.464
Oh, no, no, no, no!

41:48.547 --> 41:50.049
-Hey, what?
-[Diego] No!

41:50.132 --> 41:52.510
-Klaus, why are you bringing Ben here?
-Come on!

41:52.593 --> 41:55.346
-Hear me out before--
-Hear him out.

41:55.429 --> 41:58.015
The brother that you all knew as Ben

41:58.098 --> 41:59.058
is gone.

41:59.141 --> 42:01.936
And not-- I don't mean our Ben,
the nice Ben.

42:02.019 --> 42:03.103
I mean this Ben.

42:03.187 --> 42:05.940
The asshole, he's gone now.

42:06.023 --> 42:07.608
-Gone.
-Klaus, what are you talking about?

42:07.691 --> 42:12.696
And the man that stands
in front of you is new new Ben,

42:12.780 --> 42:16.450
and he's one of us,
and he's a member of the team.

42:16.534 --> 42:19.995
-And he's part of the family!
-…part of the family!

42:20.079 --> 42:23.707
And as a welcome gift,
I suggest we throw him off the roof.

42:23.791 --> 42:25.042
-Yeah. I'll help.
-Come on.

42:25.125 --> 42:26.669
You know what? You know what?

42:27.294 --> 42:29.713
-He can stay. He can stay.
-Why?

42:29.797 --> 42:33.384
'Cause it's my wedding day, man.
Come on. He can stay.

42:33.467 --> 42:35.010
[Ben and Klaus] Yes!

42:35.094 --> 42:37.012
[Klaus] I knew it, I knew it.

42:37.096 --> 42:39.682
Hey, big guy. Awfully nice of you.

42:39.765 --> 42:41.600
Yeah, you're… you're welcome.

42:41.684 --> 42:43.269
Ooh! Whoa!

42:43.769 --> 42:45.187
Holy smokes.

42:45.729 --> 42:48.107
[pensive string music playing]

42:58.242 --> 42:59.994
Hey, you know something?

43:00.077 --> 43:02.454
Tonight is all I ever really wanted.

43:03.998 --> 43:05.291
To get hitched?

43:06.000 --> 43:10.546
Just… everybody coming together
when it really matters.

43:13.173 --> 43:15.968
One big real family.

43:27.563 --> 43:29.356
[coughs, retches]

43:29.440 --> 43:30.899
[all] Whoa! Whoa!

43:30.983 --> 43:33.027
Oh, I think I'm gonna hurl.
[stomach rumbles]

43:33.110 --> 43:34.570
[all laughing]

43:34.653 --> 43:35.654
[Five] Actually, uh,

43:36.780 --> 43:37.740
I think I'm hungry.

43:37.823 --> 43:40.659
See ya, guys. I'm gonna hit the buffet.

43:40.743 --> 43:41.785
Is he gonna be okay?

43:41.869 --> 43:44.830
-It's Five. What do you think?
-Maybe we should call it a night.

43:44.913 --> 43:47.207
-Come on, it's early.
-[Lila] Good night, guys.

43:47.291 --> 43:49.251
-Where we going? To bed?
-The night's young.

43:49.335 --> 43:50.252
Who is this guy?

43:50.336 --> 43:51.462
[Klaus] Ben.

43:51.545 --> 43:54.006
-[Luther chuckles]
-Where's he going? Where's he going?

43:54.089 --> 43:55.215
This isn't the end.

43:56.842 --> 43:58.761
-[sighs]
-[Klaus] Come on, who's up for some more…

43:58.844 --> 44:01.430
-[Ben] Scrabble?
-[Klaus] …karaoke. Yeah!

44:01.513 --> 44:02.848
That's my cue.

44:02.931 --> 44:04.058
[chuckles]

44:05.059 --> 44:06.185
-Good night.
-Night.

44:10.522 --> 44:11.732
[Luther sighs]

44:11.815 --> 44:14.318
[distant explosions booming]

44:23.452 --> 44:25.204
[dramatic string music playing]

44:27.081 --> 44:28.707
[stomach gurgling]

44:28.791 --> 44:30.209
[clanging]

44:30.292 --> 44:31.627
[vomiting]

44:31.710 --> 44:33.587
[Reginald] With everything
we've discussed,

44:33.671 --> 44:35.339
it'd be folly to wait.

44:36.131 --> 44:37.424
There is no time.

44:38.092 --> 44:39.426
I can't do this without you.

44:39.510 --> 44:41.220
[heartbeat thumping]

44:41.303 --> 44:42.388
Do we have a deal?

44:42.471 --> 44:44.431
[heartbeat thumping rapidly]

44:44.515 --> 44:47.059
[dramatic music swelling]

44:48.185 --> 44:49.812
-[bell dings]
-[elevator door opens]

44:52.481 --> 44:53.399
[thuds]

44:56.068 --> 44:59.988
[rock violin music playing]
